title: PewDiePie tops list of highest-paid YouTube stars
text:
PewDiePie tops list of highest-paid YouTube stars 
Maane Khatchatourian, Variety.com Friday, October 16, 2015 11:48 AM EDT | Updated: Friday, October 16, 2015 12:08 PM EDT In this Oct. 28, 2013 file photo, Felix Kjellberg, aka PewDiePie, arrives at the Los Angeles premiere of "Ender's Game" at TCL Chinese Theatre in Los Angeles. (Photo by Matt Sayles/Invision/AP, File) Report an error 
LOS ANGELES - Gaming's crown prince PewDiePie is king of YouTube celebrities. 
The video-game-playing bro, who's birth name is Felix Kjellberg, is the world's highest-paid YouTube star, having earned $12 million over the past year and thereby topping Forbes magazine's first-ever ranking of the top-paid stars on the Google video platform. 
The 25-year-old Swedish star has nearly 40 million YouTube subscribers. 
PewDiePie also topped Variety's list of Famechangers, the digital world's top 12 stars whose influence stands head and shoulders above the rest. 
The duos of Smosh, Ian Hecox and Anthony Padilla, and the Fine Brothers, Benny and Rafi Fine, were runner-ups with $8.5 million. 
Violinist Lindsey Stirling came in fourth with $6 million. Comedians Rhett and Link -- aka Rhett McLaughlin and Charles Lincoln Neal III -- and video game commentator Olajide Olatunji -- known as "KSI" -- tied for fifth $4.5 million. 
Make-up artist Michelle Phan was seventh at $3 million. 
Comedian Lilly Singh -- called "Superwoman" -- prankster Roman Atwood and chef Rosanna Pansino tied for eighth with $2.5 million. 
Here's the full list: 
2. (Tie) Smosh and Fine Brothers: $8.5 million 
4. Lindsey Stirling: $6 million 
5. (Tie) Rhett & Link and KSI: $4.5 million 
7. Michelle Phan: $3 million 
8. (Tie) Lilly Singh, Roman Atwood, Rosanna Pansino: $2.5 million Sponsored Links
